Method Overloading ---> If a class contains more than one method with the same name is called a Method Overloading.

Constructor Overloading ---->If a class contains more than one constructor it is called Constructor Overlaoding.


IF we define same method multiple time it will conflict, therefore there are some rule whioch we foolow in Method Overloading.
Rules to follow:-- for both MethodOverlaoding & Constructor

1) Number of Parameters
2) Order of Parameters 
3) data type of parameters




Constructor -----> A constructor is a type of a method which is having the same name of the class. 
				   A constructor will not return any value 
				   A Constructor will be invoked at the time of execution.( We don't need to call the constructor explicitely)
				   A Constructor will take the parameters(just like a method)
				   A Constructor is used for initialising the values.
				   

Type of Constructor:- 

1) Default Constructor ( without any parameters) 

2) Parametrised Constructor


--------------------------------------------------------------------

IMPORTANT:- We can also overload the main method 

class Test {

public static void main(String[] args) {
		
	
	//In order to over load the main metbod we need to change the parameters
	
	
public static void main() {

// code 

} 

public static void main(int a, int b) {

//code 

}

}				



---------------------------------------------------------------------------


this keyword ----->  this keyword is used to eliminate the confusion between class attributes and parameters with the same name 























